Diagnosis (
Bock 1931
) emended : Cryptocelidae with oblong-oval body shape, with or without tentacles. Paired cerebral and tentacular eye clusters present. Pharynx central. True seminal vesicle connected to the prostatic vesicle by a narrow duct. Interpolated large prostatic vesicle, elliptic, with numerous secretory ducts. Unarmed penis papilla. Weak muscular vagina, with or without a vestigial Lang’s vesicle, with the common oviduct clearly differentiated.
